{"title_page": "Adrian Lewis Morgan", "text_new": "{{Short description|Welsh actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Adrian Lewis Morgan\n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name          = Adrian Lewis Morgan\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1972|2|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Beddau]], Wales\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years active       = \n| spouse             = {{Marriage|Ria Morgan|2010}}\n| children           = 1\n| education          = [[Royal Welsh College of Music & Drama]]\n}}\n'''Adrian Lewis Morgan''' (born 22 February 1972)<ref name=\"Details\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/drama/doctors/actors/adrian_lewis_morgan_person_page.shtml|title=Adrian Lewis Morgan (Jimmi)|work=[[BBC]]|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref> is a Welsh actor, known for portraying the role of [[Jimmi Clay]] in the [[BBC One|BBC]] soap opera ''[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]''. Having appeared since 2005, he is the longest serving cast member on ''Doctors''.<ref name=\"metro\">{{cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2017/08/25/when-is-bbc-one-tv-show-doctors-back-on-6876270/|title=When is BBC One TV show Doctors back on?|date=25 August 2017|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nMorgan was born in [[Beddau]] on 22 February 1972,<ref name=\"Details\" /> and has one sister.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s16/doctors/interviews/a31459/adrian-lewis-morgan.html|title=Adrian Lewis Morgan|work=[[Digital Spy]]|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref> He graduated from the [[Royal Welsh College of Music & Drama]].<ref name=\"metro\" /> In 1998, Morgan was involved in a car accident.<ref name=\"Details\" />\n\n==Career==\nMorgan's first role was as [[Tobias Ragg]] in ''[[Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street|Sweeney Todd]]'' at the [[Royal National Theatre]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theatricalia.com/play/5je/sweeney-todd/production/d5f|title=Production of Sweeney Todd|website=Theatricalia|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref> During his theatre career, he starred in various [[West End theatre|West End]] productions, including: [[Marius Pontmercy|Marius]] in ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (musical)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''; Roger in ''[[Rent (musical)|Rent]]''; and Judas/Annas in ''[[Jesus Christ Superstar]]''.<ref name=\"Details\" /> From 2001 to 2002, he appeared in the [[BBC One|BBC]] medical drama ''[[Holby City]]'' as [[Liam Evans (Holby City)|Liam Evans]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/13fXCDJ10qHc6gC02kLLJTW/jimmi-clay|title=BBC One - Doctors - Jimmi Clay|website=BBC|language=en-GB|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref> Since 2005, he has portrayed the role of [[Jimmi Clay]] in the BBC daytime soap ''[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.walesonline.co.uk/lifestyle/showbiz/adrian-lewis-morgan-2000th-episode-doctors-1852074|title=Adrian Lewis-Morgan on the 2,000th episode of Doctors drama|work=[[Wales Online]]|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref> He is the longest serving cast member on ''Doctors''.<ref name=\"metro\" />\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2001\u20132002\n| ''[[Holby City]]''\n| [[Liam Evans (Holby City)|Liam Evans]]\n| Series regular\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]''\n| Andy Rees\n| Episode: \"Sleeping Dogs\"\n|-\n| 2005\u2013present\n| ''Doctors''\n| [[Jimmi Clay]]\n| Series regular\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Result\n! Ref(s)\n|-\n| 2010\n| [[Inside Soap Awards|''Inside Soap'' Awards]]\n| Best Daytime Star\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/news/a242852/in-full-inside-soap-awards-2010-nominees.html |title=In Full: Inside Soap Awards 2010 Nominees |last=Wightma