rittney]], [[Amanda Abbington]], [[Tilly Keeper]], [[Aiysha Hart]], [[Nina Sosanya]] and [[Emma Rigby]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2020-04-02/bbc-three-drama-make-me-famous-first-look/amp/|title=First look at BBC Three one-off drama about impact of \"fast fame\" on reality TV stars|work=[[Radio Times]]|date=2 April 2020|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nBilly finds both fame on a constructed-reality series. When he impresses the producers of the series, he believes his life is set to change forever. A year after the show has been broadcast, many of Billy's co-stars are doing well in their career, but Billy struggles to balance the fame, social media and the assumptions people have made about him, which result in him having self-confidence issues.<ref name=\"Tilly\">{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/04/01/tilly-keepers-first-role-since-leaving-eastenders-revealed-12492792/amp/|title=Tilly Keeper's first role since leaving EastEnders revealed|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|date=2 April 2020|access-date=2 April 2020|last=Patterson|first=Stephen}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Tom Brittney]]<ref name=\"Belfast\">{{Cite news|url=https://amp.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/film-tv/news/grantchesters-tom-brittney-to-play-lead-role-in-bbc-three-drama-make-me-famous-39096126.html|title=Grantchester's Tom Brittney to play lead role in BBC Three drama Make Me Famous|work=[[Belfast Telegraph]]|date=1 April 2020|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Amanda Abbington]]<ref name=\"Belfast\" />\n* [[Tilly Keeper]]<ref name=\"Tilly\" />\n* [[Aiysha Hart]]<ref name=\"Belfast\" />\n* [[Nina Sosanya]]<ref name=\"Belfast\" />\n* [[Emma Rigby]]<ref name=\"ED\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.entertainmentdaily.co.uk/news/eastenders-tilly-keeper-new-role/?format=amp|title=Former EastEnders star Tilly Keeper lands first role since leaving soap|work=Entertainment Daily|last=Rodrigues|first=Charotte|date=2 April 2020|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Trieve Blackwood-Cambridge<ref name=\"ED\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 television films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2020 television film by Peter King}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Make Me Famous\n| image                = \n| genre                = <!-- Must be reliably sourced -->\n| creator              = [[Reggie Yates]]\n| writer               = Reggie Yates\n| producer             = Margaret Conway<ref name=\"TVWise\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvwise.co.uk/2020/04/tom-brittney-amanda-abbington-aiysha-hart-nina-sosanya-more-to-star-in-bbc-threes-make-me-famous/|title=Tom Brittney, Amanda Abbington, Aiysha Hart, Nina Sosanya & More To Star In BBC Three\u2019s 'Make Me Famous'|work=TVWise|date=2 April 2020|access-date=10 April 2020|last=Munn|first=Patrick}}</ref>\n| director             = Peter King<ref name=\"TVWise\" />\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Tom Brittney]]\n* [[Amanda Abbington]]\n* [[Tilly Keeper]]\n* [[Aiysha Hart]]\n* [[Nina Sosanya]]\n* [[Emma Rigby]]\n* Trieve Blackwood-Cambridge\n}}\n| country              = United Kingdom\n| language             = English\n| executive_producer   = {{Plainlist|\n* Colin Barr\n* Sue Horth\n}}\n| editor               =\n| camera               = Multi-camera\n| runtime              = 60 minutes\n| company              = Expectation Entertainment\n| network              = [[BBC Three]]\n| released             = 2020\n| related              = ''[[Killed by My Debt]]''\n}}\n'''''Make Me Famous''''' is an upcoming British television film that is expected to premiere on [[BBC Three]] in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2020/cast-announced-reggie-yates-make-me-famous|title=Cast announced for Reggie Yates\u2019s screenplay: BBC Three\u2019s Make Me Famous|work=[[BBC]]|date=2 April 2020|access-date=